external_knowledge:
- "creators" refers to the `user_name` of the users who created the test cases;
- "living essence" metaphorically represents the core elements of the test cases, including their names (`test_case_name`) and descriptions (`description`);
- "functional seeds" are test cases categorized as 'functional';
- "blossomed into the realms of both XForms Basic and XForms Full" means the test cases are normative for both XForms Basic (`xforms_basic = 1`) and XForms Full (`xforms_full = 1`);
- "still flourish within the garden of active projects" implies the status of these test cases is 'active'.

- "specs starting with '4.'" refers to specification names starting with the prefix "4.".;
- "crafted" refers to the creation of test cases by users. ;
- "how many times each test case has been performed" indicates the frequency of test results associated with each test case. ;
- "ranked by the most active ones" means sorting the results in descending order of the count of test results for each test case.

; 'past year' refers to the year 2023 in this context;
; 'frequency of failing attempts' is represented by the count of failed test results;
; 'average compatibility with XForms standards' is derived from averaging the boolean values of `xforms_basic` and `xforms_full`;
; 'variety of categories' denotes the count of unique categories a test case belongs to;
; 'most recent update date' is the latest `last_modified_date` for each test case;
